<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-07-23T21:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-07-23T21:00:00-05:00" n="520" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d520">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.50A/42: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName type="from">Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-07-24T10:00:00+08:00">July 24, 1933—10
                                a.m.</date><lb/>[Received July 24—2:25 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>618. Department’s 252, July 21, noon.<note n="20" xml:id="d520fn20">Not
                                printed; it reported telegrams No. 138, July 15, 9 p.m., from the
                                Secretary of State, in London, and No. 329, July 18, 5 p.m., from
                                the Ambassador in France.</note> In this connection please see my
                            294, March 30, 5 p.m. Rajchman’s connection with League plan will in my
                            opinion doom effort of League to the suspicious attention and opposition
                            of the Japanese.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>